[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1773},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F12\u002F15\u002Fdiscord-bot-with-openai-gpt3\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F12\u002F15\u002Fdiscord-bot-with-openai-gpt3\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F12\u002F15\u002Fdiscord-bot-with-openai-gpt3\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F12\u002F15\u002Fdiscord-bot-with-openai-gpt3\u002F":1748,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2022\u002F12\u002F15\u002Fdiscord-bot-with-openai-gpt3\u002F":1757},"\u002Fnodejs\u002F20221215\u002F2411869749\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":1730,"date":1731,"description":1732,"extension":1733,"lang":1734,"meta":1735,"navigation":398,"path":1736,"readingMinutes":1737,"seo":1738,"standalone":1739,"stem":1740,"tags":1741,"tldr":1744,"updated":1745,"url":1746,"__hash__":1747},"content\u002Fen\u002FNodejs\u002Fdiscord-bot-with-openai-gpt3.md","Building a Discord Chatbot with OpenAI GPT-3","2418697423",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":1716},"minimark",[11,16,20,38,42,45,48,66,69,73,82,89,92,98,101,107,115,118,124,127,133,136,142,145,151,154,157,164,167,170,176,179,185,188,191,197,202,205,209,212,255,258,284,305,312,315,319,322,327,330,590,593,621,636,639,658,681,885,895,901,904,908,919,1262,1265,1287,1297,1309,1558,1565,1571,1576,1580,1583,1591,1594,1603,1606,1612,1615,1618,1621,1625,1628,1635,1639,1642,1665,1668,1672,1675,1690,1697,1704,1712],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"This post walks through building a Discord chatbot using OpenAI GPT-3 — one that can reply to your messages. Discord is actually a really good fit for integrating with OpenAI. The main focus is GPT-3, but the sample repo also includes GPT-3.5 commits for reference.",[21,22,23],"blockquote",{},[17,24,25,29,30,37],{},[26,27,28],"strong",{},"Warning","\nYou'll need to apply for your own OpenAI Key. For the application process, see ",[31,32,36],"a",{"href":33,"rel":34},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002Fnodejs\u002F20221210\u002F1224824056\u002F#%E7%94%B3%E8%AB%8B-OpenAI-API",[35],"nofollow","this post (article in Mandarin)",".",[12,39,41],{"id":40},"preamble","Preamble",[17,43,44],{},"I'm not going to cover Node.js, Git, GitHub, npm basics in this post — it'd get way too long.",[17,46,47],{},"But if you're not familiar with npm and Git commands, here are some earlier posts (in Mandarin):",[49,50,51,59],"ul",{},[52,53,54],"li",{},[31,55,58],{"href":56,"rel":57},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002Fhexo\u002F20200921\u002F849819598\u002F",[35],"(8) Try Learning Hexo - Basic npm commands you should know (article in Mandarin)",[52,60,61],{},[31,62,65],{"href":63,"rel":64},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002Fgit\u002F20190615\u002F1148594701\u002F",[35],"Basic Git commands (article in Mandarin)",[17,67,68],{},"I'll include the sample code GitHub link at the end, with README notes so you can quickly run a Discord bot yourself.",[12,70,72],{"id":71},"discord-setup","Discord setup",[17,74,75,76,81],{},"First step — create a Discord bot. Go to the ",[31,77,80],{"href":78,"rel":79},"https:\u002F\u002Fdiscord.com\u002Fdevelopers\u002Fapplications",[35],"Discord Developer Portal"," and click Application.",[17,83,84],{},[85,86],"img",{"alt":87,"src":88},"Application","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fa0Od41t.png",[17,90,91],{},"Click \"New Application\".",[17,93,94],{},[85,95],{"alt":96,"src":97},"New Application","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FaEa0M5F.png",[17,99,100],{},"It'll ask for a bot name — let's go with \"OpenAI GPT-3\".",[17,102,103],{},[85,104],{"alt":105,"src":106},"OpenAI GPT-3","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FcFSnLzP.png",[21,108,109],{},[17,110,111,114],{},[26,112,113],{},"Note","\nThis is the application name, not the bot's display name. It'll also become the role name on your Discord server, so pick something good.",[17,116,117],{},"Inside the \"OpenAI GPT-3\" application page, we need to create a bot. Click \"Bot\" on the left.",[17,119,120],{},[85,121],{"alt":122,"src":123},"Bot","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FbaUchls.png",[17,125,126],{},"Click \"Add Bot\" on the right.",[17,128,129],{},[85,130],{"alt":131,"src":132},"Add Bot","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FvnpXA5Y.png",[17,134,135],{},"Discord asks you to confirm. Click \"Yes, do it!\".",[17,137,138],{},[85,139],{"alt":140,"src":141},"Yes, do it!","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FN6LdkrN.png",[17,143,144],{},"Your bot now appears. Find the \"Token\" field and click \"Reset Token\".",[17,146,147],{},[85,148],{"alt":149,"src":150},"Reset Token","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FA5iTEwZ.png",[17,152,153],{},"You'll get a Token string — your bot's Token. Save it, we'll need it later.",[17,155,156],{},"Don't share your bot Token with anyone — they could take control of your bot.",[17,158,159,163],{},[160,161,162],"code",{},"Username"," will be your bot's display name. In my sample code, I called mine \"妙麗·格蘭傑\" (Hermione Granger).",[17,165,166],{},"Important — scroll down to find \"Privileged Gateway Intents\" and turn on \"Message Content Intent\", otherwise the bot can't receive messages.",[17,168,169],{},"Next, add the bot to your Discord server. Click \"OAuth2\" on the left, then \"URL Generator\" (the easier method).",[17,171,172],{},[85,173],{"alt":174,"src":175},"URL Generator","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FLtQioGX.png",[17,177,178],{},"In the \"SCOPES\" section, check \"bot\". In \"BOT PERMISSIONS\", check \"Send Messages\".",[17,180,181],{},[85,182],{"alt":183,"src":184},"Send Messages","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FeiUZwyz.png",[17,186,187],{},"We only need the bot to reply to messages, so only \"Send Messages\" is needed. If you want more functionality, check additional permissions.",[17,189,190],{},"Below you'll see a \"Generated URL\" section. Copy that URL, paste into your browser, hit Enter. You'll see a screen for choosing which server to add the bot to. Pick yours and add the bot.",[17,192,193],{},[85,194],{"alt":195,"src":196},"Add to Bot","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FePRXynz.png",[17,198,199],{},[85,200],{"alt":195,"src":201},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FpbMp7A7.png",[17,203,204],{},"Bot's now in your server. Basic Discord bot setup done.",[12,206,208],{"id":207},"project-environment","Project environment",[17,210,211],{},"Create a folder — let's call it \"discord-bot\" — and initialize:",[213,214,219],"pre",{"className":215,"code":216,"language":217,"meta":218,"style":218},"language-bash shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","mkdir discord-bot\ncd discord-bot\nnpm init -y\n","bash","",[160,220,221,234,243],{"__ignoreMap":218},[222,223,226,230],"span",{"class":224,"line":225},"line",1,[222,227,229],{"class":228},"s_sBn","mkdir",[222,231,233],{"class":232},"sTRMh"," discord-bot\n",[222,235,237,241],{"class":224,"line":236},2,[222,238,240],{"class":239},"sCcAr","cd",[222,242,233],{"class":232},[222,244,246,249,252],{"class":224,"line":245},3,[222,247,248],{"class":228},"npm",[222,250,251],{"class":232}," init",[222,253,254],{"class":239}," -y\n",[17,256,257],{},"Install the packages we need:",[49,259,260,268,276],{},[52,261,262,263],{},"dotenv\n",[49,264,265],{},[52,266,267],{},"Reads .env files",[52,269,270,271],{},"discord.js\n",[49,272,273],{},[52,274,275],{},"For Discord operations",[52,277,278,279],{},"openai\n",[49,280,281],{},[52,282,283],{},"For OpenAI GPT-3 operations",[213,285,287],{"className":215,"code":286,"language":217,"meta":218,"style":218},"npm install dotenv discord.js openai\n",[160,288,289],{"__ignoreMap":218},[222,290,291,293,296,299,302],{"class":224,"line":225},[222,292,248],{"class":228},[222,294,295],{"class":232}," install",[222,297,298],{"class":232}," dotenv",[222,300,301],{"class":232}," discord.js",[222,303,304],{"class":232}," openai\n",[17,306,307,308,311],{},"Create ",[160,309,310],{},"index.js"," in the project root — that's where we'll write the bot code.",[17,313,314],{},"(Consider adding ESLint to keep your code quality in check.)",[12,316,318],{"id":317},"writing-the-code","Writing the code",[17,320,321],{},"The fun part. I won't comment every line, but I'll keep it simple so you can build your own bot.",[323,324,326],"h3",{"id":325},"discord-bot","Discord bot",[17,328,329],{},"First, the Discord bot code. Discord.js's npm page has an example:",[213,331,335],{"className":332,"code":333,"language":334,"meta":218,"style":218},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","const { Client, GatewayIntentBits } = require('discord.js');\nconst client = new Client({ intents: [GatewayIntentBits.Guilds] });\n\nclient.on('ready', () => {\n  console.log(`Logged in as ${client.user.tag}!`);\n});\n\nclient.on('interactionCreate', async interaction => {\n  if (!interaction.isChatInputCommand()) return;\n\n  if (interaction.commandName === 'ping') {\n    await interaction.reply('Pong!');\n  }\n});\n\nclient.login(TOKEN);\n","js",[160,336,337,375,394,400,423,455,461,466,491,518,523,540,559,565,570,575],{"__ignoreMap":218},[222,338,339,343,347,350,353,356,359,362,366,369,372],{"class":224,"line":225},[222,340,342],{"class":341},"sWyjQ","const",[222,344,346],{"class":345},"sMAXC"," { ",[222,348,349],{"class":239},"Client",[222,351,352],{"class":345},", ",[222,354,355],{"class":239},"GatewayIntentBits",[222,357,358],{"class":345}," } ",[222,360,361],{"class":341},"=",[222,363,365],{"class":364},"sj_SG"," require",[222,367,368],{"class":345},"(",[222,370,371],{"class":232},"'discord.js'",[222,373,374],{"class":345},");\n",[222,376,377,379,382,385,388,391],{"class":224,"line":236},[222,378,342],{"class":341},[222,380,381],{"class":239}," client",[222,383,384],{"class":341}," =",[222,386,387],{"class":341}," new",[222,389,390],{"class":364}," Client",[222,392,393],{"class":345},"({ intents: [GatewayIntentBits.Guilds] });\n",[222,395,396],{"class":224,"line":245},[222,397,399],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":398},true,"\n",[222,401,403,406,409,411,414,417,420],{"class":224,"line":402},4,[222,404,405],{"class":345},"client.",[222,407,408],{"class":364},"on",[222,410,368],{"class":345},[222,412,413],{"class":232},"'ready'",[222,415,416],{"class":345},", () ",[222,418,419],{"class":341},"=>",[222,421,422],{"class":345}," {\n",[222,424,426,429,432,434,437,440,442,445,447,450,453],{"class":224,"line":425},5,[222,427,428],{"class":345},"  console.",[222,430,431],{"class":364},"log",[222,433,368],{"class":345},[222,435,436],{"class":232},"`Logged in as ${",[222,438,439],{"class":345},"client",[222,441,37],{"class":232},[222,443,444],{"class":345},"user",[222,446,37],{"class":232},[222,448,449],{"class":345},"tag",[222,451,452],{"class":232},"}!`",[222,454,374],{"class":345},[222,456,458],{"class":224,"line":457},6,[222,459,460],{"class":345},"});\n",[222,462,464],{"class":224,"line":463},7,[222,465,399],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":398},[222,467,469,471,473,475,478,480,483,486,489],{"class":224,"line":468},8,[222,470,405],{"class":345},[222,472,408],{"class":364},[222,474,368],{"class":345},[222,476,477],{"class":232},"'interactionCreate'",[222,479,352],{"class":345},[222,481,482],{"class":341},"async",[222,484,485],{"class":228}," interaction",[222,487,488],{"class":341}," =>",[222,490,422],{"class":345},[222,492,494,497,500,503,506,509,512,515],{"class":224,"line":493},9,[222,495,496],{"class":341},"  if",[222,498,499],{"class":345}," (",[222,501,502],{"class":341},"!",[222,504,505],{"class":345},"interaction.",[222,507,508],{"class":364},"isChatInputCommand",[222,510,511],{"class":345},"()) ",[222,513,514],{"class":341},"return",[222,516,517],{"class":345},";\n",[222,519,521],{"class":224,"line":520},10,[222,522,399],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":398},[222,524,526,528,531,534,537],{"class":224,"line":525},11,[222,527,496],{"class":341},[222,529,530],{"class":345}," (interaction.commandName ",[222,532,533],{"class":341},"===",[222,535,536],{"class":232}," 'ping'",[222,538,539],{"class":345},") {\n",[222,541,543,546,549,552,554,557],{"class":224,"line":542},12,[222,544,545],{"class":341},"    await",[222,547,548],{"class":345}," interaction.",[222,550,551],{"class":364},"reply",[222,553,368],{"class":345},[222,555,556],{"class":232},"'Pong!'",[222,558,374],{"class":345},[222,560,562],{"class":224,"line":561},13,[222,563,564],{"class":345},"  }\n",[222,566,568],{"class":224,"line":567},14,[222,569,460],{"class":345},[222,571,573],{"class":224,"line":572},15,[222,574,399],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":398},[222,576,578,580,583,585,588],{"class":224,"line":577},16,[222,579,405],{"class":345},[222,581,582],{"class":364},"login",[222,584,368],{"class":345},[222,586,587],{"class":239},"TOKEN",[222,589,374],{"class":345},[17,591,592],{},"What this does:",[49,594,595,600,605,615],{},[52,596,597,599],{},[160,598,349],{},": the Discord Client — what we use to interact with Discord's API",[52,601,602,604],{},[160,603,355],{},": Discord's GatewayIntent — defines what our bot does",[52,606,607,610,611,614],{},[160,608,609],{},"client.on('ready', () => { ... })",": what to do when the bot starts — e.g. print \"",[160,612,613],{},"Logged in as ${client.user.tag}!","\" to tell us the bot is ready",[52,616,617,620],{},[160,618,619],{},"client.login(TOKEN)",": log in with the bot's Token from the Discord Developer Portal",[17,622,623,624,627,628,631,632,635],{},"The important pattern is ",[160,625,626],{},"client.on('Event', () => { ... })",". The ",[160,629,630],{},"Event"," is what we listen to. ",[160,633,634],{},"ready"," listens for bot startup.",[17,637,638],{},"Discord has many events — common ones:",[49,640,641,646,652],{},[52,642,643,645],{},[160,644,634],{},": bot has started",[52,647,648,651],{},[160,649,650],{},"interactionCreate",": user invokes a bot command",[52,653,654,657],{},[160,655,656],{},"messageCreate",": user sends a message",[17,659,660,661,663,664,666,667,670,671,663,674,677,678,680],{},"These are the most common. We only need ",[160,662,634],{}," and ",[160,665,656],{},". We also need to set ",[160,668,669],{},"intents"," — what the bot is allowed to do. We need ",[160,672,673],{},"GuildsMessages",[160,675,676],{},"MessageContent",", so modify the example like this in ",[160,679,310],{},":",[213,682,684],{"className":332,"code":683,"language":334,"meta":218,"style":218},"require('dotenv').config()\n\nconst { Client, GatewayIntentBits } = require('discord.js');\n\nconst client = new Client({ intents: [\n  GatewayIntentBits.Guilds,\n  GatewayIntentBits.GuildMessages,\n  GatewayIntentBits.MessageContent,\n]});\n\nclient.on('ready', () => {\n  console.log(`Logged in as ${client.user.tag}!`);\n});\n\nclient.on('messageCreate', async message => {\n  console.log('User message:', message.content);\n});\n\nclient.login(process.env.DISCORD_TOKEN);\n",[160,685,686,705,709,733,737,752,757,762,767,772,776,792,816,820,824,846,860,865,870],{"__ignoreMap":218},[222,687,688,691,693,696,699,702],{"class":224,"line":225},[222,689,690],{"class":364},"require",[222,692,368],{"class":345},[222,694,695],{"class":232},"'dotenv'",[222,697,698],{"class":345},").",[222,700,701],{"class":364},"config",[222,703,704],{"class":345},"()\n",[222,706,707],{"class":224,"line":236},[222,708,399],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":398},[222,710,711,713,715,717,719,721,723,725,727,729,731],{"class":224,"line":245},[222,712,342],{"class":341},[222,714,346],{"class":345},[222,716,349],{"class":239},[222,718,352],{"class":345},[222,720,355],{"class":239},[222,722,358],{"class":345},[222,724,361],{"class":341},[222,726,365],{"class":364},[222,728,368],{"class":345},[222,730,371],{"class":232},[222,732,374],{"class":345},[222,734,735],{"class":224,"line":402},[222,736,399],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":398},[222,738,739,741,743,745,747,749],{"class":224,"line":425},[222,740,342],{"class":341},[222,742,381],{"class":239},[222,744,384],{"class":341},[222,746,387],{"class":341},[222,748,390],{"class":364},[222,750,751],{"class":345},"({ intents: [\n",[222,753,754],{"class":224,"line":457},[222